      • AddObjectCellRange

        public void AddObjectCellRange(java.util.List<java.lang.Object> values,
                               Cell.Address startAddress,
                               Cell.Address endAddress)
                        throws UnknownRangeException,
                               UndefinedStyleException
        Adds a list of object values to a defined cell range. If the type of the a particular value does not match with one of the supported data types, it will be casted to a String
        Note: Due to limitations of Java generics can this group of methods not be defined as overloading method with a single function name. Each inner type needs distinct function name.
        Parameters:
        values - List of unspecified objects to insert
        startAddress - Start address
        endAddress - End address
        Throws:
        UndefinedStyleException - Thrown if the default style was misconfigured
        UnknownRangeException - Thrown if the next cell is out of range (on row or column)

      • addObjectCellRange

        public void addObjectCellRange(java.util.List<java.lang.Object> values,
                               java.lang.String cellRange)
                        throws FormatException,
                               UnknownRangeException,
                               UndefinedStyleException
        Adds a list of object values to a defined cell range. If the type of the a particular value does not match with one of the supported data types, it will be casted to a String
        Parameters:
        values - List of unspecified objects to insert
        cellRange - Cell range as string in the format like A1:D1 or X10:X22
        Throws:
        FormatException - Thrown if the passed address is malformed
        UndefinedStyleException - Thrown if the default style was misconfigured
